# Update and Install Git on the VM so that we can create a local repo and connect to the remote repo on GitHub 
Method -
Use the following commands
sudo apt-get update (should show Done)
sudo apt-get install git ( should show Done)
git --version ( This will show the version of the Git installed if succesful)
git init (this initializes an empty repo)
git config --global user.name "yourname" ( enter your username here)
git config --global user.email "your email here " ( enter your email here)
git config --list ( this will show your name and email)
Wow now you are ready to add, commit and push files from this local repo to your remote repo!!!

